 key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:106945-0!canonical and timestamp 20220511110801 and revision id 14242141. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{Gone|update=PvM QoL updates & Wilderness Rejuvenation improvements}}\n{{Infobox Item\n|name = Demon's heart\n|image = [[File:Demon's heart (balance).png]]\n|release = [[23 November]] [[2017]]\n|update = Mage Arena II, Revenant Caves & Deadman Beta\n|removal = [[8 February]] [[2018]]\n|removalupdate = PvM QoL updates & Wilderness Rejuvenation improvements\n|members = Yes\n|quest = [[Mage Arena II]]\n|tradeable = No\n|placeholder = Yes\n|equipable = No\n|stackable = No\n|noteable = \n|destroy = You will have to locate and defeat another demon.\n|examine = The heart torn from the chest of the Demon of Balance.\n|value = 14\n|weight = 0.3\n|id = hist21798\n}}\n[[File:Demon's heart (balance) detail.png|left|180px]]\nA '''demon's heart''' was a drop from the [[Demon of Balance]]. This heart, along with the hearts of [[demon's heart (light)|light]] and [[demon's heart (darkness)|darkness]] from the [[Demon of Light]] and [[Demon of Darkness]] respectively, was required to imbue a [[god cape]] during the [[Mage Arena II]] [[miniquest]].\n\nSubsequent imbues would require only one heart of the player's choice, in which this heart would imbue a [[Guthix cape]] into an [[Imbued guthix cape]].\n\nThe demon's heart could not be deposited into a [[bank]], and was '''always''' lost upon death, so it was recommended to turn it in to [[Kolodion]] as soon as possible.\n\n==Item sources==\n{{Drop sources|Demon's heart (balance)}}\n\n{{Mage Arena II}}"}